06763nam a22008415i 9783110733228DE-B159720211027022714.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211027t20212021gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97831107332287 a10.1515/97831107332282doi  a(DE-B1597)575075  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE04aThe Arts of the Grid :bInterdisciplinary Insights on Gridded Modalities in Conversation with the Arts /ced. by Liora Bigon, Nava Shaked. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2021] 4c©2021  a1 online resource (XV, 239 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContent -- tList of Illustrations -- tForeword: On Grids and Networks -- tAcknowledgements -- t1 Introduction ‒ The Arts of the Grid: Interdisciplinary Insights on Gridded Modalities in Conversation with the Arts -- t2 The Networked Artwork: The Grid as Dynamic Relational Form? -- tPart I: Planting and Planning the Grid -- t3 The Grid Specialized: Practical Town Planning, Artistic Features, and Natural Settings in Twentieth-Century Brazilian New Towns -- t4 Centrifugal or Processional: Divine and Mundane Power in Ancient Chinese Funeral Grids -- t5 Globalizing Senegal’s Grid-Plan Legacies in Light of Islamic Studies, World History and Urban Studies -- tPart II: Generating Grids of Computational Arts -- t6 Between Technological and Aesthetic Grids: Philosophical Challenges Posed by AI Artists -- t7 Sounds in Grid: History and Development of Grid-Based Musical Interfaces and their Rooting in Sound, Interaction and Screen Design -- t8 On Grids of Contemporary Art Production: A Convergence of Artistic, Computational, Craft and Performative Making -- tPart III: Kinetic Grids: Bridging, Digging, Floating -- t9 Searching for the Grid at the Turn of the Nineteenth Century: When Art and Science Shared their Fragments -- t10 Depth as Grid: An Improvisational Actor’s Perspective -- t11 How to Do Things with Grids: Anarchitectures of Navigability -- tPart IV: Grids of Learning: Linguistic, Virtual, Visual -- t12 The Linguistics Relation in the Virtual Grid: A Digital Dialogue -- t13 Storytelling in Virtual Reality: A Multidisciplinary and Immersive Experience using Grid Methodology for Students -- t14 The Multidisciplinary Learning Grid: A Conceptual Space to Develop Neuropedagogy-based, Arts-integrated Chemistry Activities -- t15 Concluding Remarks: Grids of Light, Darkness, and Intermediate Shades -- tAbout the Contributors -- tAbout the Participant Artists0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis is the first collection of interdisciplinary scholarship to expand on gridded modalities, with a strong affinity to the arts. It seeks to inspire new avenues of research by exploring a horizon of gridded relationships among humans, between humans and the environment, and between human and non-human actors. By bringing together philosophical themes and applied practices, the volume traces a genealogy of the "grid" as an exercise in grasping its inherent complexity and incomplete quality. A collective effort by a group of researchers, practitioners, and designers, it promotes an understanding of gridded modalities as complex networks that interact with other networks, generating new meanings and reflecting changes in thought.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 4aDigitale Kunst. 4aKünstliche Intelligenz / Kunst. 4aLandschaftsgestaltung. 4aStadtgestaltung.  aurban and landscape design, computational and artificial intelligence art, performing and media arts.1 aAlkobi Fishman, Sagit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBauer, Frank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBigon, Liora, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabu